    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>April 12. 5609</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours <date>3d.</date> inst to hand, for which<lb/> I offer many
                thanks.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Since my last the congregation agreed to have<lb/> a temporary place
                of worship opened. <persName>Mr. de Silva</persName><lb/> officiated on <date>1<hi
                        rend="sup">st</hi> days of <hi rend="underline">Pesach</hi></date> &amp;
                will continue so that<lb/> after all my first proposition has been adopted.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I note your remarks about <persName>Gutheim</persName>. You<lb/> are
                in error in thinking that you had previously<lb/> answered my inquiries. Like myself
                you have<lb/> been forgetful &amp; not sufficiently explicit several<lb/> times. I
                have always made full allowances<lb/> for your inadvertence &amp; knowing what I
                have<lb/> recently undergone you ought to do the same<lb/> for me. Respecting the
                inscription I am<lb/> happy that you have given me right. With<lb/> regard to the
                Organ, you “did the thing” just<lb/> as I wanted it, neither too much nor too
                little.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will please have the <add>נר תמר</add> made to<lb/>
                <add>?</add> into the ceiling of the ark, between<lb/> the cornice &amp; the sliding
                doors</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please procure a “Shophar” &amp; also<lb/> a
                    <date><sic>Hanuca</sic></date> lamp.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Regarding the number of bells for<lb/> the sepharim, please get even
                so 5<lb/> in all; the last two <hi rend="underline">perhaps</hi> you may<lb/> as
                well have made somewhat <hi rend="underline">plainer</hi> if there<lb/> is any great
                difference in cost; if not then<lb/> let them be like others.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>You will please have the table covers<lb/> made as you <sic>pupise</sic> sixty three
                by forty four inches.</p>
            <p
                rend="Diagram of table cover, noting that it should be 63 inches by 44 inches in size."/>
            <p>I believe I have said all that is necessary<lb/> above. It is proper to add that as a
                matter<lb/> of form I asked my old friend <persName>Mr Touro</persName><lb/> if he
                approved of the above to which he answered<lb/> as usual that I must take the blame
                or credit<lb/> of everything.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As to the convention I spoke of it to<lb/> every Jew I met with
                &amp; the German Congre<lb/>gation had already acted as I wanted mine to do<lb/> but
                some of my wiseacres preferred taking<lb/> two weeks to consider about it, so we
                hold<lb/> an adjourned meeting next <date>Sunday</date> to decide<lb/> on the
                matter. I shall insist on sending<lb/> a delegate &amp; I think when I talk to
                them<lb/> as I intend to in opening the meeting,<lb/> there will be little farther
                hesitancy.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would have sent you a telegraph<lb/> ie dispatch as you request,
                but<lb/> on inquiry at the telegraph office<lb/> find that the wires are down
                bet<lb/>ween <placeName>Mobile</placeName> &amp; <placeName>Montgomery</placeName>
                so we would<lb/> lose 2 &amp; perhaps 3 days, therefore concluded<lb/> to write by
                mail at once to day.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Hebrew Benevolent Association<lb/> at last annual meeting
                elected me<lb/> President. They require some one<lb/> to take the lead again for a
                while<lb/> to get things straight, to draft a<lb/> constitution &amp; by laws fit
                for the<lb/> government of such a society, &amp; to procure<lb/> a charter. I know
                there was great diss<lb/>atisfaction &amp; fearing that the society<lb/> might be
                dissolved I accepted the<lb/> office which I held <del>from</del> for the two
                first<lb/> years of its existence. The duties are severe<lb/> &amp; take up a great
                deal of time if properly performed.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have had two very disagreeable questions<lb/> to decide &amp; act
                upon in my congregation, which<lb/> when we meet or I have more time I shall<lb/> be
                happy to communicate &amp; ask your opinion<lb/> on my judgment &amp; acts in the
                premises.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Will you be so kind as to inform me how <persName>L A<lb/> Levy
                    Jr.</persName> who married <persName>Isabella Levy</persName> of <placeName>New
                    York</placeName> is affected<lb/> by his <hi rend="underline">legal</hi> though
                    <hi rend="underline">illegal</hi> marriage. He is a Levite<lb/> &amp; I presume
                his marriage is not recognized by<lb/> us in calling him to “sephar” in “Schule”.
                Yet<lb/> if we “do not go behind the curtain” he has a regular<lb/> “Ketuba”. His
                offspring I know we regard as “momscien<add>?</add>”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">He is a very good man but I will act according<lb/> to our law to
                the letter. Do give my fond love to my dear little<lb/> aunt husband &amp;c when you
                see them &amp; believe me yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">G. Kursheedt</persName>.</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>My worthy old friend <persName>Mr Touro</persName> received your<lb/> letter in due
                course acknowledging<lb/> receipt of draft. He desires me to<lb/> forward his best
                respects to you<lb/> I have to send this letter by the extra mail to
                    <placeName>Mobile</placeName><lb/> may it reach you in the enjoyment of perfect
                health</p>
            <p rend="The 3 lines are written sideways in the center of the page."/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Penna</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>In a week or two I shall know pretty well<lb/> whether or not I shall see you in
                    <date>June</date>.<lb/> If I do not leave here I will write you<lb/> at length
                on the subject of securing<lb/> a lecturer for the congregation</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">truly yours I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">GK</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
